#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.9"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.9:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.9:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 9. Vajjiputtasutta → vajjīputtasuttaṃ (s2, s3) | vajjīputto (vesalī) (pts1)
msgctxt "sn9.9:0.3"
msgid "9. Vajjiputtasutta"
msgstr "9. A Vajji"

# BB has “Vajjian prince”, which is an unwarranted intrusion from the comm.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.202"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.9:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ aññataro vajjiputtako bhikkhu vesāliyaṃ viharati aññatarasmiṃ "
"vanasaṇḍe."
msgstr ""
"At one time a certain Vajjian mendicant was staying near Vesālī in a certain "
"forest grove."

msgctxt "sn9.9:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ vajjiputtako sabbaratticāro hoti."
msgstr "Now at that time the Vajjis were holding an all-night event in Vesālī."

msgctxt "sn9.9:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so bhikkhu vesāliyā tūriyatāḷitavāditanigghosasaddaṃ sutvā "
"paridevamāno tāyaṃ velāyaṃ imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then that mendicant, groaning at the noise of musical instruments being "
"beaten and played, on that occasion recited this verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.435"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.9:2.1"
msgid "“Ekakā mayaṃ araññe viharāma,"
msgstr "“We dwell alone in the wilderness,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: Apaviddhaṃva → apaviṭṭhaṃva (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn9.9:2.2"
msgid "Apaviddhaṃva vanasmiṃ dārukaṃ;"
msgstr "like a cast-off log in the forest."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.9:2.3"
msgid "Etādisikāya rattiyā,"
msgstr "On a night like this,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: nāmamhehi → nāma amhehi (bj, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn9.9:2.4"
msgid "Ko su nāmamhehi pāpiyo”ti."
msgstr "who’s worse off than me?”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.9:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tassa bhikkhuno anukampikā "
"atthakāmā taṃ bhikkhuṃ saṃvejetukāmā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"The deity haunting that forest had compassion for that mendicant, and wanted "
"what’s best for them. So they approached that mendicant wanting to stir them "
"up, and addressed them in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.9:4.1"
msgid "“Ekakova tvaṃ araññe viharasi,"
msgstr "“You dwell alone in the wilderness,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.9:4.2"
msgid "Apaviddhaṃva vanasmiṃ dārukaṃ;"
msgstr "like a cast-off log in the forest."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.9:4.3"
msgid "Tassa te bahukā pihayanti,"
msgstr "Lots of people are jealous of you,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.9:4.4"
msgid "Nerayikā viya saggagāminan”ti."
msgstr "like beings in hell of those going to heaven.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.9:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho so bhikkhu tāya devatāya saṃvejito saṃvegamāpādīti."
msgstr ""
"Impelled by that deity, that mendicant was filled with a sense of urgency."
